[1
Date: 11 Oct 2000
From: M. Cosgriff <mcosgriff@hotmail.com>
Source: Australian Broadcast Co., 11 Oct 2000 [edited

The French Food Safety Agency has recommended a total ban on the use of cow
intestines in food production. The proposal follows fears of a spread of
BSE (Bovine Spongiform Encephalopathy, Mad Cow Disease) in the country.
More than 50 cases have been diagnosed since the beginning of the year. The
Agency says the method of cleaning the intestines, which are primarily used
as sausage skins, does not guarantee full protection against the spread of
the disease which has been linked to a fatal human illness.
